        "question": "Does taking the stool occult test hurt in any way?  ",
        "answer": "Not at all. This test is simple and pain free."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I do the test while on my periods?",
        "answer": "Menstrual blood during the test could potentially give inaccurate results, so you should take it only after your periods."
      },
      {
        "question": " Is the stool occult test still okay for people with hemorrhoids? ",
        "answer": "Yes, but sometimes they lead to positive tests when that is not the case."
      },
      {
        "question": "Any plans on what to do next in case I result positively?  ",
        "answer": "After a positive result, your medical professional will explain the following options, like colonoscopy or other examinations."
      }
